ref: https://hackernoon.com/docker-tutorial-getting-started-with-python-redis-and-nginx-81a9d740d091

- 1 application = 1 container
- run the process in the foreground (don't use systemd, upstart, etc)
- keep data out of containers, use volumes. Do not use SSH (if you need to step into a container, use `docker exec`)
- avoid manual configurations (or actions) inside container.
